# How to set up a simple python HTTP server in your Red Hat VM

* Start the server in whatever directory with `python -m http.server` and it should start listening on port `8000`
* [Change firewall settings](20230818132416) to allow access to port 8000 from another machine
* Open up a browser on the host and go to `http://<guest-ip>:8000` and you should see the directory contents

